// instrNoChangesContract is the shared NoChangesContract (TD-031 §8.1) rule.
// When the agent writes no_changes_rationale.txt the loop now refuses to close
// the bead unless the rationale carries one of the structured markers below.
const instrNoChangesContract = `

## no_changes contract

If you write ` + "`{{.AttemptDir}}/no_changes_rationale.txt`" + `, the loop will only close the bead as ` + "`already_satisfied`" + ` when the file carries one of these markers:

- ` + "`verification_command: <shell command>`" + ` — a single-line shell command the loop runs (cwd = project root, 60s timeout). The loop closes the bead iff the command exits 0. Include the command's actual output below the marker as evidence.
- ` + "`status: needs_investigation`" + ` paired with ` + "`reason: <why you cannot make progress>`" + ` — the bead stays open with a triage label so an operator (or auto-triage) can take over.

A rationale that carries neither marker is rejected: the bead stays open with a ` + "`triage:no-changes-unjustified`" + ` label. "Bare" no_changes ("nothing to do", "looks done already") is no longer accepted — either prove the AC is met with a verification_command or declare needs_investigation with a reason.`

